div.div: When a User starts a Playground, the details are fetched from MongoDB and if the User is authenticated and verified, an ECS Container is launched in Fargate with its Environment Variables containing Signed S3 GET and PUT URLs to access the saved Playground files. The IP Address of this Container is then mapped to a Slug and this mapping is stored in Redis. The Slug is Returned to the User.

div.div: The User connects to the container by querying the DNS Server with the Slug. The DNS Server looks up the Slug from Redis and maps the URL to the IP Address of the Container by creating an "A" DNS Record. The Reverse Proxy also adds a route to the Container's Preview URL to a URL with SSL.
